gomodel:67c10cc400000031
        a                 owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "BRD4 recruits P-TEFb (which contains CDK9) to acetylated chromatin, facilitating its interaction with target genes15. The C-terminal P-TEFb-interacting domain (PID) of BRD4 directly increases CDK9's catalytic activity. " ;
